{"/service/ndnp/okhi/batch_okhi_hughes_ver01/data/sn85042345/0023728432A/1921021801/0618.xml":{"full_text":"TULSA DAILY WOULD, SPRING OIL TRADE EDITION\nSpend a Little Save a Little. Get Business Back to Normal\n!B jC Li E S F I Li L JSm\nWHA T BIG BUSINESS IS DOING\nPHILLIPS PETROLEUM\nCOMPANY\nFIRST NATIONAL BANK BLDG.\nBARTLESVILLE, OKLA.\nHigh Grade\nPetroleum\nProducts\nThe\nEmpire\nCompanies\nSUBSIDIARY CITY SERVICE CO.\nMasonic-Empire Bldg.\nBartlesville, Oklahoma\nThe Bartlesville\nClearing House Association\nComposed of Five\nProgressive Banks\nCombined Deposits $10;000,000.00\nCombined Resources Ovcr....$12,000,000.00\nThe present financial\nstrength of the members\nof this Association\nreflects the sound\nindustrial condition\nof our community.\nBARTLESVILLE -THE CITY OF OPPORTUNITY\nIt is perhaps unnecessary to direct attention of Okla\nhomans to any particular part of Oklahoma. It is\nonly necessary to open our eyes and see. Neverthe\nless, it is worth while to think on these things which\nhave been developed in the state within a very brief\nspace of time.\nThe advertisers whose names appear on this space\narc but a very few of the many strong and progres\nsive growing institutions of this city. These, as well\nas many others have been built on a permanent basis,\nand in these strenuous times of business depression\nare secure because of the substantial way in which\nthey have conducted their business.\nBartlesville has always enjoyed a very steady, sub\nstantial and permanent growth. Its streets arc paved,\nits schools are erected, its homes arc built, its busi\nness life is conducted, its social life is enjoyed, and\nits moral and religious life is organized with an idea\ntoward a definite future development and pros\nperity. No city can take more pride in its develop\nment than Bartlesville, and no city can show more\nto be proud of that Bartlesville.\nBartlesville a few years ago heard the call of 'Oppor\ntunity.\" It has proved to be a city of opportunity and\nthe fact of its development during these brief years\nshows very vividly that it has \"buildcd well.\" Bar\ntlesville has grown from a struggling village to a\ncity of some twenty thousand people having within\nits midst a number of industries, and invites new in\nvestors who are looking for a city where opportunity\nis open for big development.\nHere, within the limits of the city, was drilled the\nfirst oil producing well of the state. Though it was\ndrilled in 189G it is still producing, thus proving that\nthe Bartlesville oil field is of long and permanent en\ndurance. While it is true that Bartlesville is an oil\ncenter, yet it is located in one of the most fertile\nregions of the stale for all agricultural development.\nWe have need for more farmers. The opportunity is\nhere, the virgin soil is here, and it is but necessary\nto apply the disposition and desire to till the soil,\nand the story of success will begin in this line.\nBartlesville has a strong Chamber of Commerce\nworking for the advancement of the community and\ncity. Any inquiry directed to this body will receive\ncareful consideration and authentic information.\nW i\n\nIndian Territory Illuminating Oil Co.\nNEW MASONIC BLDG.\nBartlesville, Okla.\nMeridian Petroleum Corporation\nProdu cers Refiners Transporters\nGasoline Naphtha\nGas Oil Fuel Oil\n600 S.R. Cylinder Stock\nKerosene\nWax Distillate\nBlended Gasoline\nUnlit .'r I'll\nREFINERIES\nOkmulgee, Oklahoma.\nPonca City, Oklahoma\nHominy, Oklahoma\nGENERAL OFFICES\nRialto Building\nKansas City\nMissouri\nBRANCH OFFICES\nMayo Building\nTulsa, Oklahoma, and\nBartlesville, Oklahoma\nBlack, Sivalls Bryson\nOil and Water\nTANKS\nOFFICES:\nBartlesville, Okla., Tulsa, Okla.\nIndependence, Kan.\nH. V. Foster Interests\nOil and Gas\nNew Masonic BIdg.\nBartlesville, Okla.\nHOTEL MAIRE\nAs might be expected in a city with the wealth\nand class of Bartlesville, a modern high class\nhotel is most necessary. In this city is found ono of\nthe most modern, fireproof hotels in the state and\nwhich would be a credit to any metropolitan city.\nIn order to make the life of the oil operator more\ncomplete Mr. M. It. Puckctt, lesseo and proprietor\nof the Maire Hotel, has provided the following\nluncheon program for private dining room:\nMONDAY\nAllolo (Ladlca) Club\nTIJK8DAY\nT'lil ncita-Tltota Alumni Club\nAlso Chamber of Oommerno\nWKD.S'KHDAY\nKlwanla Club\nn lunar) ay\nnotary Cloli\nl'lUDAY\nMerchants' Dlvinlon Cliarn\nbcr nf Commerce\nBATUUDAY\nWnBhlnston County Bar Association.\n7","height":"24856","width":"21148"}}
